<h2 class="post-title"><a href="https://random.brunosan.eu/beautiful-video-for-nasa-by-reidgower-alanmla">Beautiful video for NASA by @reidgower.</a></h2>
<div class="copy" id="post_39968750">
<div class="posterous_bookmarklet_entry">
<object height="300" width="500">
<param name="movie" value="https://www.youtube.com/v/oY59wZdCDo0&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1&amp;hd=1"/>
<param name="wmode" value="window"/>
<param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"/>
<param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"/><embed src="https://www.youtube.com/v/oY59wZdCDo0&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1&amp;hd=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="opaque" height="300" width="500"></embed>
</object>
<div class="posterous_quote_citation">via <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oY59wZdCDo0">youtube.com</a></div>
<blockquote class="posterous_medium_quote">
<p>"We who can even put our own planetary home in order, riven with rivalries and hatreds. Are we to venture into space? [...] For all our failings, despite our limitations and fallibilities, we humas are capable of greatness." <br/>[Carl Sagan, Pale blue dot]</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Indeed the bar for NASA outreach is set very high. Frustrated with the poor use of social media by NASA, Reid Gower decided to put together this video using a few videos from the Internet. Beautiful work.</p>
<blockquote class="posterous_medium_quote">
<p>"I got frustrated with NASA and made this video. NASA is the most fascinating, adventurous, epic institution ever devised by human beings, and their media sucks. Seriously. None of their brilliant scientists appear to know how to connect with the social media crowd, which is now more important than ever. In fact, NASA is an institution whose funding directly depends on how the public views them."</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
